  "prompt": "Will the Indian customs department charge customs tax for a Rs90,000 DSLR camera bought in the USA?",
  "response": "Yes, the Indian customs department will likely charge customs duty on a DSLR camera brought into India from the USA. In general, electronic items like cameras are subject to customs duty when brought into India. The exact amount depends on several factors:\n\n1. Value of the camera\n2. Type of camera\n3. Purpose of import (personal use or commercial)\n4. Duration of stay in India\n\nFor personal use, there are some duty-free allowances, but for a high-value item like a Rs 90,000 camera, you will likely need to pay customs duty. The typical customs duty for electronic items can range from 20-40% of the item's value.\n\nTo get the exact duty amount, you should:\n1. Carry original purchase invoice\n2. Declare the item at customs\n3. Be prepared to pay applicable duties\n4. Consider consulting a customs broker for precise calculations\n\nRecommendation: Check the current customs regulations or consult with Indian customs officials for the most up-to-date and accurate information specific to your situation.",
